## TASK-008: Search Tie-Free Witnesses - Complete

### Search Space
| Parameter | Value |
|-----------|-------|
| Graph type | connected simple undirected labeled graphs |
| Vertex range | 1 to 4 |
| Sample constraint | each graph vertex appears exactly once (no duplicates) |
| Labelings | all binary labelings |
| Orderings | all permutations of vertex set |
| k parameter | 1 |

### Tie-Free Condition Definition
- **Condition**: For every prediction used in accepted LOO and replace-one witness records, the relevant query point has a unique nearest sample occurrence
- **Applies to**:
  - Original sample before perturbation
  - Perturbed sample after LOO deletion or replace-one replacement

